{
  "stem": "1020.1",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Isidore Hollander.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I-S-A-D-O-R-E H-O-L-L-A-N-D-E-R.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Hollander.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And my Yiddish nomer was Yitzhak Doff.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "When I was  born, it was spelled in French.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Actually, my name-- my parents' name was the spelling H-O-L-E-N-D-E-R, I was born in Paris.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And my mother received me after birth with my birth certificate, H-O-L-L-A-N-E-D-E-R.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And coming to the United States, we changed the name as it is now.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "1920.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I'm going to be 75 July 26.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, my parents came to Paris 1919.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I was born 1920.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And then, my father became ill.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He was told that he is not going to survive.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Those years was very hardship in France, in Paris, to be buried in a Jewish cemetery.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So as my father was raised as an orthodox, he wanted to go back home to Poland.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "A matter of fact, when he left and I was age three-- 1923-- he only lived two weeks, and he passed away.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That's why we stayed in Poland.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My mother never went back to France.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, we were coming back to Poland.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Four years-- I was with my mother up to age seven.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And my mother went through with us, with me and a sister of mine-- an older sister, which she's perished-- a lot of not good four years.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And finally, she found somebody to get married after being four years a widow.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And it happen the stepfather wasn't too much agreeable with my mother to keep us at home, me and my sister.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So my mother gave me away to an orphanage, to a Jewish orphanage, in hometown of Bendin.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Which, thanks to those good years that I was in the orphanage, I was raised as a mensch.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I was educated in Yiddish and the Polish language.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "In the 1930s, we possessed in the orphanage already a Chumash-- translated in Polish like, we have in here in English.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And we used to follow the codex of Janusz Korczak, the one that went with his children in Warsaw with the orphanages to Treblinka.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And we were raised very well-disciplined.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 6 SECONDS] I didn't have a father, but I don't regret that I was in the orphanage.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Because who knows would have-- what come out out of me when I would have been with my stepfather.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Well, I finished public school in the orphanage.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "I finished three years evening school.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "That's part of high school.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And I learned a trade-- I learned to be a tailor, ladies' garments.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And I worked till the end of-- till the beginning of the War, till 1939.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And I left the orphanage.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "I already start to make a little living.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "So Hitler came in and interrupted young life, age 19.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "I was told a story before, a little story, that 1936, as I was born in France, and I had aunts and friends with cousins-- which I was twice visiting them after the war, my mother's sisters-- and I was trying to get away from Poland, because we knew already that we have a enemy.",
      "word_count": 55
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "Hitler-- we start to read about, get educated about.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "So I figured, maybe I'll go away from Poland.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "I'll go to France.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And I smuggled myself.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And I was caught in a German town, Breslau.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And I was taken to the police.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And an officer in the brown shorts slapped me in my face.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And he told me that we have enough the Jews-- swines in here.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "We don't need another one.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "You go back.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "He slapped me.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "And he go back and he said, tell your friends and the other swines that we will follow.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "Well, I couldn't-- I couldn't go back the same path I went.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "But I had to go back to Czechoslovakia.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "When I came back, I used to belong to a Zionist organization, [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "When I start to tell them what I was told in Germany, when I was slapped by going back, they thought that I'm bringing propaganda and I'm going to panic the Jewish people.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "And nobody believed that somebody like me-- 16 years of age-- could come up with such a lie-- that is what I was told.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "But unfortunate, it happened that they did follow.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "And it was too late to believe.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, yes.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We went home every Saturday afternoon, all the children go home to their parents.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We had to come back in the evening, up to age 14. 15, we slept in the orphanage-- but as of limited space.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "When we become 14, they located us to Jewish people.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Let's say, was a-- a woman, a widow-- she had an extra room, they paid for it from the Jewish community that she gave us-- like, me and another friend, not far from the orphanage, which we located.",
      "word_count": 38
    }
  ],
